          <type>const char *</type>
          <declname>psz_action2</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>const char *</type>
          <declname>psz_title</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>const char *</type>
          <declname>psz_fmt</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>...</type>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Asks a total (Yes/No/Cancel) question</para>
<para>This function waits until the user dismisses the dialog or responds. It&apos;s interruptible via vlc_interrupt. In that case, <ref refid="group__vlc__dialog_1ga41302d6e505ed5c80a76666cb8758bc9" kindref="member">vlc_dialog_cbs.pf_cancel()</ref> will be invoked. The psz_cancel is mandatory since this dialog is always cancellable by the user.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>p_obj</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>the VLC object emitting the dialog </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>i_type</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>question type (severity of the question) </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>psz_cancel</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>text of the cancel button </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>psz_action1</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>first choice/button text (optional) </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>psz_action2</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>second choice/button text (optional) </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>psz_title</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>title of the question dialog </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>psz_fmt</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>format string for the question message </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>&lt; 0 on error, 0 if the user cancelled it, 1 on action1, 2 on action2 </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
